    <h2>Gaggenau in LA — BSH ultra-luxury for architectural custom kitchens</h2>
    <p>Gaggenau's US positioning targets a specific segment: architect-designed custom kitchens where the appliance suite is part of the architectural program rather than a product purchase. The Gaggenau design language emphasizes geometric precision, solid stainless materials, minimalist visible controls — particularly evident in the Series 400 Vario cooktop modular system and the integrated fully-panel-ready dishwasher architecture. LA Gaggenau service geography maps directly onto the architecturally-significant custom-kitchen demographic: Beverly Hills / Bel Air / Holmby Hills major remodels designed by LA architects for discerning owners; Pacific Palisades canyon estates; Hollywood Hills homes with architectural provenance; Encino / Calabasas / Hidden Hills Valley estate kitchens; Newport Coast / Corona del Mar OC luxury.</p>
    <p>Our service approach for Gaggenau emphasizes respect for the installation's architectural integration. Panel-ready trim + adjacent cabinetry preservation during service matters particularly on Gaggenau because the surrounding custom cabinetry typically represents significant additional investment beyond the Gaggenau appliance itself. We coordinate with the homeowner's general contractor or cabinet carpenter when a service call requires removing the dishwasher from cabinetry for rear-access repair.</p>
